    "en": {
      "title": "UNESCO Award for Chinese Neuroscientist",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) has awarded 49-year-old Chinese neuroscientist Hu Hylan the 2022 UNESCO Women's Award for Science for her contribution to the development of the next generation of antidepressant drugs.",
        "She and four other scientists received the award at the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) headquarters in Paris on Thursday evening.",
        "Hu, a professor and executive director of the Center for Neuroscience at Zhejiang University's College of Medicine, is one of the youngest recipients of the award to date and the 7th Chinese to receive such an award since its establishment in 1998.",
        "The other four winners this year are Maria Guzman of Cuba, Catalin Carico of the United States, Agnes Binagoho of Rwanda and Angela Nieto of Spain, according to UNESCO."
      ],
